Fact tables & Populate the Fact Tables 16

Click on the SSIS packages under the Solution Explorer and select new SSIS Package and give the appropriate name.

Create Source and Destination Manager –

• Right Click on the Connection Manager Window in the bottom and select New OLE DB Connection from the menu to make new connection manager.

 

 

• Click New for new connection manger to configure

• Configure the connection on the 

Server name – Your SQL Server name

Connect to a database – select or enter the Database from the dropdown option, select the Source database name and Test the connection by clicking on the Test connection button.

• After testing the connection click OK.


 

• Repeat the Steps for creating the new connection manager for destination. In the select or enter a database name option choose the destination database.


1. DFT - FactIncidentReport

Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Drag and drop the Data Flow - right click Rename it as DFT - FactIncidentReport.

Double click the Data Flow Task –

·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Source – Double click and add the Source connection manager and Data access mode select SQL Command – Copy the below code and paste in the SQL command text box.  And select OK

Select [Incident Number w/year],
[Call (911) Problem],
[ UCR Code],
[UCR Offense Description],
[Year of Incident],
[Month of Occurence],
[Day of the Week],
[Day1 of the Year],
[Council District],
[City],
[Zip Code],
[Responding Officer #1  Badge No],
[Victim Race],
[Victim Name],
[Victim Age],
[Watch],
[Reporting Area],
[Beat],
[Sector],
[Time of Occurrence]
from DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging

·         Drag and drop the derived column - use the Derived column Code and add the as shown in the Gif – Use the code below fig for creating the columns 


·         Drag and drop Lookup and rename it as IncidentKey and double click to configure as follows

3.     Columns tab – make connection Source to destination as shown in fig and select OK

·         Make a Copy of the Lookup and then connect the First lookup to the copied lookup – select the option shown below-


·         Double click the 2nd lookup to go the Column Tab – unselect the IncidentReportKey and Match the Column from the source’s column to that in destination’s columns as shown in fig.


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Command and make connection from the copied lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.


·         Double click the OLE DB command to configure it

1.     Connection Manager Tab – connect to the destination connection manager

2.     Component Properties Tab – in the SQL command – copy and paste the below code   and select OK

Update FactIncidentReport
set
[VictimAge] =?,
[Watch] =?,
[ReportingArea] =?,
[Beat] =?,
[Sector] =?,
[DayofYear] =?,
[TimeOccurred] =?,
[RecordFlag] =1,
[Effectivedate] = getdate(),
[EndDate] = getdate()-1
where [IncidentReportKey] =?

 

3.     Column Mapping Tab – select the input column as shown in below fig and select OK


·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Destination and make connection from the FactIncidentReportKey lookup to it – make connection as shown below fig.


·         Double click on the OLE DB Destination to config it

1.     Connection manager Tab – OLE DB Connection manager – Select the Destination connection manager & Name of the Table or View – Select the FactIncidentReport table

2.     Mapping Tab – Connect the Column as shown in fig and Select OK



2. DTF- FactInvestigationReport

Using SSIS Toolbox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard:

Drag and drop the Data Flow - right click Rename it as DFT - FactInvestigationReport.

Double click the Data Flow Task –

·         Drag and drop the OLE DB Source – Double click and add the Source connection manager and Data access mode select SQL Command – Copy the below code and paste in the SQL command text box.  And select OK.

select 
 [Incident Number w/year] , 
  [Element Number Assigned], 
  [Victim Business Name], 
  [NIBRS Code], 
  [Responding Officer #1  Badge No], [Weapon Used],[Victim Name], 
  case when [Family Offense] = 0 then 0 end [Family Offense], 
  case when [Hate Crime] =
'No' then 0 when [Hate Crime] = 'Yes' then 1 else 0 end [Hate Crime], 
  [ UCR Code], 
  case when [Gang Related Offense] in ('G', 'J', 'Yes') then 1 when [Gang Related Offense] in ('No',
'UNK') then 0 else null end [Gang Related Offense], 
  Case when [Drug Related Istevencident] = 'Yes' then 1 when [Drug Related Istevencident] in ('No',
'UNK') then 0 else null end [Drug Related Istevencident], 
  [Criminal Justice Information Service Code], 
  [X Coordinate], 
  [Y Cordinate] 
from 
DallasCrimeData_Staging..DallasCrimeStaging

·         Drag and drop the derived column - use the Derived column Code and add the as shown in the Gif – Use the code below fig for creating the columns 


·         Drag and drop Lookup and rename it as IncidentKey and double click to configure as follows

1.     General tab – Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries – select Ignore Failure.

2.     Connection tab – OLE DB Connection manger – Select the destination connection manager and Use a table or a view – select DimIncidentDetails from the dropdown.

3.     Columns tab – make connection Source to destination as shown in fig and select OK

Update [dbo].[FactInvestigationReport]
set
 
[FamilyOffense] =?,
[HateCrime] =?,
[GangRelatedOffense] =?,
[DrugRelatedIncident] =?,
[CriminalJusticeInformationServiceCode] =?,
[X-Coordinate] =?,
[Y-Cordinate] = ?,
[RecordFlag] =1,
[Effectivedate] =getdate(),
[EndDate] = getdate()-1
 
where [InvestReportKey] =?

 

3.     Column Mapping Tab – select the input column as shown in below fig and select OK
